CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1781273476
OL,3,CRare dormice reintroduced into woods
OL,4,Cto help revive species
OL,6,FHazel dormice have suffered from the
OL,7,Floss of old woodlands in the past
OL,8,Fcentury, the lack of management of
OL,9,Fthose that remain, and the loss and
OL,10,Fneglect of hedgerows they use as homes
OL,11,Fand corridors through the landscape,
OL,12,Fconservationists said.
OL,14,FThe reintroduction this week by PTES
OL,15,Fand partner organisations follows the
OL,16,Frelease of 21 hazel dormice into the
OL,17,Fsame woodland on the estate last year,
OL,18,Fwhich created Leicestershire's only
OL,19,Fknown population, the charity said.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1781273476
OL,3,CRare dormice reintroduced into woods
OL,4,Cto help revive species
OL,6,FWhile the dormice released last year
OL,7,Fhave bred and appear to be settling
OL,8,Finto their new home, more have now
OL,9,Fbeen introduced to what is described
OL,10,Fas one of the finest ancient woodlands
OL,11,Fin Leicestershire to increase numbers
OL,12,Fand boost their genetic diversity,
OL,13,FPTES said.
OL,15,FIan White, dormouse and training
OL,16,Fofficer at PTES, said, "Hazel dormice
OL,17,Fhave declined by over 70% nationally
OL,18,Fsince 2000 due to habitat loss, poor
OL,19,Fwoodland and hedgerow management and
OL,20,Fclimate change.
OL,26,@xD@XOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1781273476
OL,3,CRare dormice reintroduced into woods
OL,4,Cto help revive species
OL,6,F"These figures are extremely
OL,7,Fconcerning, but over the past 30
OL,8,Fyears, our reintroduction programme,
OL,9,Falongside habitat restoration,
OL,10,Fsympathetic woodland management and
OL,11,Fmonitoring, is giving this threatened
OL,12,Fspecies a real chance of recovery.
OL,14,F"And, on a local level, by releasing
OL,15,Fmore dormice into Bradgate Park this
OL,16,Fweek, we are one step closer to
OL,17,Fcreating a larger, connected
OL,18,Fpopulation that hopefully will one day
OL,19,Fspan the whole National Forest, giving
OL,20,Ffurther cause for hope.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1781273476
OL,3,CRare dormice reintroduced into woods
OL,4,Cto help revive species
OL,6,F"Since the first release of dormice in
OL,7,Fthe woodland in June 2025, volunteers
OL,8,Fand rangers have been regularly
OL,9,Fchecking the nest boxes at Bradgate
OL,10,FPark, finding a growing number of
OL,11,Fnests, an increasing population and
OL,12,Fevidence of breeding.
OL,14,FSome 46 dormice nests were found in
OL,15,Fchecks carried out in October 2025,
OL,16,Fwhile there was evidence of breeding,
OL,17,Fwith 11 young recorded in August and
OL,18,F15 in September.
OL,26,@nD@AO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,375,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F374A1781273476
OL,3,CRare dormice reintroduced into woods
OL,4,Cto help revive species
OL,6,FJames Dymond, director of Bradgate
OL,7,FPark Trust, said, "We're hugely
OL,8,Fencouraged by how well last year's
OL,9,Fdormice have settled into their new
OL,10,Fhome, and to know there is evidence of
OL,11,Fbreeding is extremely gratifying for
OL,12,Feveryone involved in both the release
OL,13,Fand ongoing monitoring.
OL,15,F"We're thrilled that more dormice will
OL,16,Fbe joining our existing population
OL,17,Fthis year, and look forward to another
OL,18,Fsummer of nest box checks supported by
OL,19,Four fantastic volunteers and,
OL,20,Fhopefully, finding more evidence of
OL,21,Fbreeding as a result."
OL,26,@oD@SOUwD@AOU}D@VO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/9
